      <title></title>
      <link>https://arvimal.github.io/docs/linux-booting/02-boot-loaders/02-grub2/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://arvimal.github.io/docs/linux-booting/02-boot-loaders/02-grub2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Get started with GRUB2&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;get-started-with-grub2&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#get-started-with-grub2&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.certdepot.net/rhel7-get-started-grub2/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;https://www.certdepot.net/rhel7-get-started-grub2/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Note: This is an &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.certdepot.net/rhel7-rhcsa-exam-objectives/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;RHCSA 7 exam objective&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Presentation of GRUB2&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;presentation-of-grub2&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#presentation-of-grub2&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GRUB2&lt;/strong&gt; is the new Linux bootloader. &lt;strong&gt;GRUB2&lt;/strong&gt; stands for &lt;strong&gt;GR&lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;U&lt;/strong&gt;nified &lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;ootloader version &lt;strong&gt;2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As &lt;strong&gt;GRUB&lt;/strong&gt; was not maintained for some time and lacked some critical features like &lt;strong&gt;GPT&lt;/strong&gt; management needed to handle disks bigger than 2.4TB, it was decided to start a new version from scratch with modularity in mind.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
